Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The economy grew by 1.9 percent in the first quarter of this year. This after recording a growth rate of 1.4 percent in the last three months of 2021. WATCH: Economic growth | GDP moves back to 2017 levels The figures by Stats SA show manufacturing was the biggest contributor to the first-quarter growth. The sector grew by 4.9 percent in the first three months of the year.